#: ../../source/cloud/docker/attack.rst:67
msgid "攻击 Docker 守护进程"
msgstr "Attacking the Docker Daemon"

#: ../../source/cloud/docker/attack.rst:68
msgid ""
"虽然 Docker 容器具有很强的安全保护措施，但是 Docker 守护进程本身并没有被完善的保护。Docker 守护进程本身默认由 root "
"用户运行，并且该进程本身并没有使用 Seccomp 或者 AppArmor 等安全模块进行保护。这使得一旦攻击者成功找到漏洞控制 Docker "
"守护进程进行任意文件写或者代码执行，就可以顺利获得宿主机的 root 权限而不会受到各种安全机制的阻碍。值得一提的是，默认情况下 Docker "
"不会开启 User Namespace 隔离，这也意味着 Docker 内部的 root 与宿主机 root "
"对文件的读写权限相同。这导致一旦容器内部 root 进程获取读写宿主机文件的机会，文件权限将不会成为另一个问题。这一点在 "
"CVE-2019-5636 利用中有所体现。"
msgstr "Although Docker containers have strong security protections, the Docker daemon itself is not fully protected. By default, the Docker daemon runs as the root user, and the daemon process itself is not protected by security modules such as Seccomp or AppArmor. As a result, once an attacker finds a vulnerability that lets them control the Docker daemon for arbitrary file writes or code execution, they can obtain root privileges on the host without being blocked by those security mechanisms. It is also worth noting that Docker does not enable User Namespace isolation by default. This means root inside Docker has the same file read and write permissions as root on the host. Therefore, once a root process inside a container gets an opportunity to read or write host files, file permissions will not be another barrier. This is reflected in exploitation of CVE-2019-5636."

